{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 9644, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "8237", "body": "Make sure to kill all the Dragonkin on the bottom floor of the instance as Eranikus will call them to help as you begin the fight and you will wipe for sure.\r\n\r\nBesides having a lot of Hit Points and hitting fairly hard Eranikus has one big catch - he uses a sleep move that erases hate on the target that has the most hate on him. During the course of the fight he will use this two to four times probably. \r\n\r\nTo help combat this if you have a Hunter have them have their pet tank him until he does his first sleep if you have a Hunter. If not assign an offtank to get aggro until he does his first sleep. Once he does the initial sleep have the maintank taunt and start getting aggro on him. When the maintank goes down if aggro does not go to your offtank then have everyone use threat reducers (Feign Death, Cat Form Cower, Paladin Bubble, Fade, Vanish, Feint, etc.) to get aggro onto the offtank.\r\n\r\nBesides the Sleep he's just a boss that hits hard and has a lot of HP. The battle can take a while, but it's not overly difficult.", "date": "2006-12-07T20:34:46-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "He's a real g, lol", "creationdate": "2013-09-29T17:14:25-05:00", "id": 697436, "rating": -1, "commentid": 9644, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "sealelia", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 15730, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sware", "body": "You don't really need two tanks, if you have another melee dps class just make sure you position him the closest to Shade of Eranikus, directly under him. He will sheep the rogue instead of the warrior so he doesn't wipe aggro and go off killing casters.", "date": "2006-12-15T01:17:59-06:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "My bad, hes move is sleep not sheep.", "creationdate": "2006-12-16T09:41:16-06:00", "id": 286331, "rating": 1, "commentid": 15730, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Sware", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 16432, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "9932", "body": "A trick i have learned when fighting him is to have one person, preferably a rogue or other melee class, to stand under him the entire fight.  If you do this, this will cause him to only sleep the person under him, so your tank is free to get aggro.  Im not sure if they fixed it, but its worked for my groups many times.", "date": "2006-12-17T00:49:57-06:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 68320, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "tekneek03", "body": "Just solo'd with first attempt on 70 frost mage..\r\nhe hits hard luckily i let my water elemental tank him for a bit at first so i can dps him down and iceblock and dps him as he ran back and forth like monkey in the middle =D", "date": "2007-04-16T19:16:31-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 85512, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "50589", "body": "Just took him down 4 man with a 48 priest, 51 Warrior, 52 Warrior, and 55 mage. \r\n\r\nThe two tank strategy is nice, because if he starts hitting cloth, they die super fast. \r\n\r\nHe is tauntable, but seems to resist it quite a bit. Just have the two tanks fight for aggro, and the sleep shouldn't be a problem.", "date": "2007-05-19T03:47:18-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "for the cloth problem, just take holy pala's for healing (works as good, iff not better) and hunter for dps, they won't die quick, and with 2 tanks and 1/2 healers its easy.", "creationdate": "2007-05-22T14:23:48-05:00", "id": 298409, "rating": 0, "commentid": 85512, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "50697", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 101425, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "41208", "body": "You must kill the troll mini-bosses in the upper part first. Clear all of the drangonkin in the lower areas including the two dragons in the South corridor. Then kill Jammal'an the Prophet in the SE corridor and head back to the middle area. The two big dragons will be back but you can pull one at a time if you wait. After the two are dead head to the Southern corridor and Eranikus will be attackable.", "date": "2007-06-09T15:24:13-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 117233, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "60672", "body": "This boss is difficult if you dont have 2 tanks, he cast \"Slumber\" which banishes the target making him immune to healing and dispels and the worst part is it causes the agro to be lost (most of the time) \r\nif you have a hunter (and a pally) make sure to cast BoS on the hunter and let their pet tank for the 10 seconds that the main tank cannot because if you do not give them BoS the boss will go for Hunter instead of the pet and this will most of the time result in death X_X", "date": "2007-07-08T01:40:10-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 128882, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Delphwind", "body": "Anyone know if paladin bubble cancels the Slumber effect Eranikus casts on the tank?", "date": "2007-07-29T21:05:35-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "doesn't work.", "creationdate": "2007-07-30T19:09:36-05:00", "id": 307021, "rating": 5, "commentid": 128882, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "nonick", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 137297, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "40551", "body": "I originally posted saying that a Shaman's Tremor Totem would be effective in preventing the sleep effect from Eranikus.  However, it would seem it's not a \"true\" sleep effect, and so isn't affected by that totem.\n\nDespite this, a Shaman is still a great asset on this fight, because Grounding Totem will absorb every sleep so long as it is active (WoWWiki points out that he uses no other single-target spells).", "date": "2007-08-13T17:10:45-05:00", "rating": 36, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Grounding totem does absorb the sleep but the tank still drops agro, so the tank should be ready to taunt.", "creationdate": "2007-09-16T01:02:23-05:00", "id": 15139, "rating": 20, "commentid": 137297, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "14386", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2007-09-11T15:31:57-05:00", 1, "40551"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 142673, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "kharzakhad", "body": "We just have downed Shade of Eranikus with three people: 55 Protection Warrior and 57 Feral Druid (in bear form) dual-tanking him and 50 Priest as a healer. Not very tough fight - the key is to taunt him when he banishes one of the tanks and everything goes smooth.\r\nAnd after a fight we ended up with one happy warrior wielding [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=10847]Dragon's Call[/url] sword :)", "date": "2007-08-23T05:39:58-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 144398, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "82558", "body": "With a warlock in our group of 49-51 level'd characters, we had the voidwalker tank until the Shade first applied his sleep debuff. Then our Warrior took over and we were able to burn him down pretty fast.  He did sleep the Warrior, but by then the Shade was down to about 10% health, and we finished him off pretty handidly.", "date": "2007-08-26T15:31:15-05:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 160061, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "52432", "body": "I killed him earlier and I must say, I was very surprised to find out how easy he is.\r\n\r\nMy group:\r\nMe 53 Druid\r\n49 Druid\r\n51 Rogue\r\n54 Rogue\r\n50 Shaman\r\n\r\nI tanked w/ 3.7k HP and 4k armor.  (just MoTW)\r\nI was 'slept' 3 times, and each time it lasts around 14seconds.\r\nHe sheds his aggro on sleep, so the 54rogue picked it up.\r\nBetween the shaman and other druid nobody died.\r\n\r\nNote, on a test run, he slept the first person that attacked him.\r\n\r\nWith a normal group, or good players 52+, this should be easy.\r\n2 tanks would be ideal, but not necessary if you have enough healz.", "date": "2007-09-28T20:49:01-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 170051, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Squirrely", "body": "Immune to mage's Slow.", "date": "2007-10-16T21:23:30-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 203703, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "Xtian", "body": "I will check on this next time I'm in ST, but I'm pretty sure that the sleep is a magic debuff and thus can be dispelled by a priest.  When you wake your tank up, he/she'll still have to grab aggro again, but at least you won't have to deal with finding another tank for 15 seconds.", "date": "2007-12-19T02:54:57-06:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "True, nothing can currently dispel this effect. Did this today with an odd group: 44 resto Shaman 50 holy Pally 49 prot Pally 46 demon Lock 49 sPriest (hit 50 during instance and got VE)  The resto pally was the main heal throughout the instance until the boss. Then we rolled things around after a wipe on the boss (sPriest pulled too much aggro with no OT) and made the holy pally the OT, the shaman was main heal and the priest and lock went nuts on him. MT and OT trade aggro throughout the fight whenever the other gets sleeped. It was cake that way. Nothing we ever tried could dispel the sleep", "creationdate": "2007-12-19T02:54:58-06:00", "id": 325043, "rating": 1, "commentid": 203703, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "119515", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Pretty sure that even though it is a magic debuff it makes him immune to everything, including a dispell. That is how it was in past times anyway", "creationdate": "2007-12-27T09:54:29-06:00", "id": 21816, "rating": 5, "commentid": 203703, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "112080", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "eemm i think its holy pally", "creationdate": "2008-02-16T09:28:37-06:00", "id": 325797, "rating": 0, "commentid": 203703, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "hostage", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Doesn't seem to be dispellable by anything. PVP trinket does not work allthough it will put the trinket on cooldown without freeing you if you use under the sleep effect, using divine shield doesn't work either.", "creationdate": "2010-05-18T09:23:11-05:00", "id": 164081, "rating": 3, "commentid": 203703, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Serrah", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 234764, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Rarehunter", "body": "Apparently, the sleep CAN be dispelled by priests, but only if you use Mass Dispel. Since this is a level 70 priest spell, your group most likely will not have this handy.\r\n\r\nI'll need someone to confirm this.", "date": "2008-02-13T00:20:12-06:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I was able to dispel sleep in ST. Can't recall if that was Eranicus sleep or of trash dragonkins. So only thing I can confirm is that if you get down everything, he's pretty much T&S.", "creationdate": "2009-01-11T15:22:35-06:00", "id": 379650, "rating": 1, "commentid": 234764, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "AnrDaemon", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 247907, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "76340", "body": "Felt curious if it was possible to kill this guy at level 70 without bothering with the dragon-thrash, except for the closest group of drakes I was able to get him down just before the rest arrived as a feral druid, a rogue with Vanish might just have a less painful time doing this however ;)", "date": "2008-03-04T13:14:00-06:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
