{"commentv2": 1, "number": 22, "id": 347994, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "149707", "body": "I'm not trying to be offensive to the blizzard people or anything but what is with the dragon keeping on talking to me after i killed him? can anyone answer this?", "date": "2008-08-08T22:09:51-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "If you completed the quest [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=3373]The Essence of Eranikus[/url] and use the trinket rewarded by it, Eranikus will whisper you telling you that you are hurting him. more info at [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=10455#comments]Chained Essence of Eranikus[/url] final comment.", "creationdate": "2008-08-14T08:23:17-05:00", "id": 43172, "rating": 4, "commentid": 347994, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "193307", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 348684, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "119112", "body": "It IS possible to off tank him with a rogue when the MT gets banished, with proper healing", "date": "2008-08-09T19:25:41-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 440042, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Evilhealbot", "body": "Something I've not seen mentioned here is that, if you have a Paladin Tank (or any other Paladin prepared to stand in front of the boss and get hit in the name of group success) but no other form of Tank capable class, the banish mechanic in this encounter can be circumvented by using Divine Shield on oneself during the cast. For the second cast, Divine Protection can be used.\r\n\r\nThis works fairly well, and allowed my group to complete the encounter successfully, but tends to fall a little short if you allow the fight to drag on for too long (more then 2 casts). Additionally, if the ability is used while forbearance is up, you will also have to deal with a loose boss. Finally, the very short cast on this abillity means that you:\r\n\r\nA) Must react very quickly to avoid it\r\nB) Are prone to being caught during the GCD, when there is nothing you can do (this may not be an issue, I can't remember whether the shields are onthe GCD or not)", "date": "2008-11-12T14:35:44-06:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 580851, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "N00bking", "body": "You must defeat Jammal'an the Prophet and  the two drakes that spawn afterwards in order to fight Eranikus.", "date": "2009-01-25T20:36:45-06:00", "rating": 59, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 617674, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "256123", "body": "Just solo'd this guy as an 80 Holy Pally...\r\n\r\nEasy enough, but I couldn't get my bubble-hearth off fast enough and I ended up being forced to fight the 50-80 dragonkin. Needless to say, within 3 min I was surrounded by a ton of corpses and was getting quite a bit of lag. Fun though...", "date": "2009-02-21T05:04:43-06:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I'm currently attempting this solo as a 52 prot paladin, and I've noticed that while he doesn't it hard, his stacking acid breath debuff really starts to sting after about 3 applications (150-200 dmg per tick) also, after being hit by deep sleep I noticed my devotion aura would be dispelled, making me waste a GCD right after deep sleep to bring it back, each time.  With only Divine Shield available to remove the debuff I think I might have to wait a level before attempting him solo again although if I was awake enough on my first attempt and used divine shield as it came off it's CD I might ha", "creationdate": "2009-02-21T05:04:44-06:00", "id": 423015, "rating": 2, "commentid": 617674, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ithuraen", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Soloed him as 55 prot paladin. Cleared the drakes first, tho :) He is so much nerfed :(", "creationdate": "2009-02-23T09:08:06-06:00", "id": 390403, "rating": 2, "commentid": 617674, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "287191", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "he must have been nerfed further since before, our warrior tanked till he was at 2/3rd when he cast the sleep like spell, myself as a 46 hunter then tanked him the last 2/3rds, there is trash in Maraudon that hits harder than him.", "creationdate": "2009-03-19T12:28:31-05:00", "id": 394895, "rating": 0, "commentid": 617674, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "327154", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yeah.....he was very, very much nerfed...I soloed him with a lvl 37 Undead Hunter.....piece of cake...  [small]EDIT: Sorry. Maybe I wasn't completely clear... I got on his [u]nerves[/u] and he tore me limb from limb....Which ofcourse for him was a piece of cake..[/small]", "creationdate": "2009-03-22T12:52:08-05:00", "id": 395485, "rating": 0, "commentid": 617674, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "283849", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "50-80? Freaking paladins... They make \"this big\" into \"THIIIIIIIIISSSSSS BIIIIIIGGGG\".   It's like saying that Hogger is soloable by a level 70 paladin. It's a level 50 instance. Soloable? Deffo?  Seriously, i am starting to hate paladins even more...", "creationdate": "2010-10-25T19:03:53-05:00", "id": 461370, "rating": 1, "commentid": 617674, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "stathisdjs", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 27, "id": 795867, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "425529", "body": "Killed him with 5 x 51 ret pallies. I didnt saw him making the sleep debuff. I bursted him down pretty fast and I noticed the mobs from the big room \"WALKED\" instead of run into the Eranikus chamber. I hugged the wall and tried to HS in the hallway from with you enter but to my suprise they runned back to their posts after a while.", "date": "2009-08-02T12:00:28-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 28, "id": 840717, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Snapperhead", "body": "Duo'd as a Prot Paladin and shadow priest, both level 50 with decent gear.\r\n\r\nAfter multiple wipes due to the pally being sleeped (can't remove with dispel magic) and the priest not able to last 12+ seconds, new tactic was pally tanks and priest stays at max range dots on eranikus, then run out down the corridor - BEFORE he slumbers the tank, while a cheap tactic perhaps, it did give slumber enough time to wear off, in which eranikus aggro'd straight back to the tank.\r\n\r\nIt took a while due to only the tank dps'ing with the occasional dot, but its the happy ending that counts.\r\n\r\nJust remember to dot up and run out before eranikus slumbers, so you have enough lead, this was our reason for demise in the first few attempts.\r\n\r\nAll in all great fun with only the two of us.", "date": "2009-09-15T07:29:07-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 29, "id": 843939, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "RingK", "body": "Soloed as Retri Paladin lvl48. Got some heirlooms and half blue/half green gear and 1hander+shield. Also for sidenote, I hadn't bought lvl48 skills yet 'cos dinged from 47 to 48 on there. \r\n\r\nWhile it does sleep me, I'm immune to all dmg so it doesn't bother much (unless interrupted heal with it). Just keep Judging and healing yourself and should be fine. Used Art of War procs for instant FoLs mainly. I had to use bubble because it stunned/interrupted one important Holy Light but survived without using LoH. I eneded up killing it with ~90% hp (~3k max) and 40% mana (~2k max).\r\n\r\nI didn't kill trash alone, might be problem for ret pally. Maybe prot pally could handle trash a bit better ^^\r\n\r\nPaladin soloing capability is insane imo., this  just strengthens my believe on it.", "date": "2009-09-19T08:29:29-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
