{"commentv2": 1, "number": 31, "id": 894446, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "115520", "body": "Tanked this guy for half the fight as a lvl 50 affli warlock, just using drain life. I was never close to dying.\r\n\r\nThink this says something about how easy Eranikus is nowadays. I remember in Vanilla when wiping 2 times or more was to be expected in a PuG.", "date": "2009-11-18T18:58:10-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 32, "id": 912739, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "495805", "body": "I bumped into this guy whilst i was Soloing the dungeon as a level 72 mage to complete some old quests. but he was just sleeping there and i could not attack him. there were no other mobs in the room. just this guy on his own and i could not attack because he was an invalid target. even though he was aggressive red.  do i have to find and kill this prophet guy first?", "date": "2009-12-10T17:03:37-06:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes, you will need to kill the prophet, and in order to summon him you must kill the ring of 6 or 7 (Can't remember) trolls upstairs.", "creationdate": "2009-12-28T16:08:37-06:00", "id": 436266, "rating": 0, "commentid": 912739, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "321609", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 33, "id": 992088, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "503764", "body": "Just wanted to point out that his eyes are always closed, indicating that he is mentally in the Emerald Dream. You can also notice that he is ghostly, similar to Ysera. I'm assuming he's being corrupted by the Emerald Nightmare.", "date": "2010-03-06T17:54:31-06:00", "rating": 15, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 34, "id": 997867, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "512042", "body": "Just solo'd this as a level 80 DK, and while it did take a while to get through, there is something fun you can do at the end. Instead of taking the mobs in the big room out, go through and stomp Eranikus and wait till they all finish piling in and use Army of the Dead and Death and Decay and watch the hilarity ensue as a giant green mob runs around the room. ^_^", "date": "2010-03-15T06:30:11-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Grats, bro. You just solo'd a level 50 dungeon.", "creationdate": "2010-05-06T19:56:16-05:00", "id": 162375, "rating": 11, "commentid": 997867, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "rosspayn3", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It's not the soloing part of the dungeon, it's the endless war chain of dragonkin mobs charging at you. I found it quite humurous on my druid.", "creationdate": "2010-06-07T21:41:44-05:00", "id": 167134, "rating": 8, "commentid": 997867, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "258919", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 35, "id": 1244787, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "selifore", "body": "I don't know why there's no map for this boss, but he's in the southeastern most area, green on the map, \"Chamber of the Dreamer\".\r\n\r\nFor some reason when I killed him not a single mob from the big room aggroed -- they just stayed where they were.", "date": "2010-12-19T03:24:11-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thank you. That's the post I was looking for!  It seems like sometimes ya gotta wade through a lot of nonsense talk to find out where to go...", "creationdate": "2011-01-01T18:50:35-06:00", "id": 471996, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1244787, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "fordahord", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It would seem that after the redesign of the dungeon, Erakinus doesn't pull any of the mobs in the big room any more, which is, in my opinion, too bad.", "creationdate": "2011-01-02T12:11:19-06:00", "id": 211010, "rating": 7, "commentid": 1244787, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Shinubi", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I believe he pulls the Drake mini-bosses. Clearing ALL the trash was downright tedious. Killing the mini bosses seems fair enough.", "creationdate": "2011-07-22T12:49:35-05:00", "id": 488771, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1244787, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Bombkirby", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 36, "id": 1309594, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "487694", "body": "The Shade of Eranikus is back up to 55 (Elite)", "date": "2011-01-25T15:30:22-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 37, "id": 1414392, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "rhinoloupe", "body": "You [b]no longer[/b] need to clear all the trash before engaging this boss. The only additional adds he will pull are his four children, the miniboss dragons.", "date": "2011-05-09T23:52:19-05:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "After a few solo clears, I wanted to clarify how it works because it's a bit odd. When you pull him, the miniboss dragons move to his location and then aggro when you're in range. So it's possible to kill him, loot him, and move away from his corpse before all 4 dragons get there. Any that don't pull into the boss fight will stay on top of the boss's corpse until you pull them.  After a bit(30-60 seconds?), dragons not aggro'd will go back to patrolling. Just watched Dreamscythe and Weaver fly back to the center of the dungeon.", "creationdate": "2011-08-03T13:23:43-05:00", "id": 256399, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1414392, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "xoxinx", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 38, "id": 1633942, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "618470", "body": "Managed to solo him (and the rest of the instance) as a level 54 hunter. I don't think he'd be possible unless you have full heirlooms though. I was using a turtle tank, BM spec obviously. Just send the pet in, activate Bestial Wrath, and both you and your pet can go all out with no problem.\n\nIt took me a few wipes to figure out how to deal with the sleep spell. I tried simply using Aspect of the Cheetah and running away shortly before he cast it, but that didn't work, as it ended up with my pet being out of range, and dying eventually.\n\nThen I changed tactic. It's easy really, just as soon as he sleeps your pet, feign death. He'll continue trying to hit your pet despite it being immune, and you can stand back up again. As long as you don't do anything, he will not reagro on you, and  then your pet can pick him up again when the sleep wears off.\n\nEDIT: Typos, because I did this at stupid-o'-clock.", "date": "2012-03-01T21:24:43-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "or a full set of rare gear. . .", "creationdate": "2012-08-17T06:09:57-05:00", "id": 564410, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1633942, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ramesh256", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-03-07T18:47:58-06:00", 1, "618470"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 39, "id": 1662276, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "lifeslowlydies", "body": "Shade of Eranikus yells:\r\n[quote]This evil cannot be allowed to enter this world! Come my children![/quote]", "date": "2012-05-03T16:39:30-05:00", "rating": 11, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 40, "id": 1700861, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Ramesh256", "body": "I soloed this (and the whole instance) as a level 58 Blood Death Knight in the Starter Zone gear. \r\n\r\nAll you have to do is stand there, get near your Bloodworms, and use Death Strike, Vampiric Blood, Rune Tap, and potions whenever you can. He dies in about 3 minutes. \r\n\r\nNote: I did Jammal'an as unholy.", "date": "2012-08-17T06:14:06-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
