{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 537491, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "230008", "body": "is he soloable at lvl 80?", "date": "2008-12-30T07:55:39-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "With 2,664,800 health, I'd say not. Just get a tank, healer and DPS and you'll probably do it.", "creationdate": "2008-12-30T15:43:56-06:00", "id": 376036, "rating": 3, "commentid": 537491, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "113424", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 551291, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "170332", "body": "[s][s]He is not soloable.[/s] Why? Because of a spell named Noxious Breath, which increases all CDs with 10 secs.[/s]\n\n[s]This goes for any of the \"Dragons of Nightmare\" as well.[/s]\n\nSeems like he CAN be soloed by some healing classes.", "date": "2009-01-07T10:51:48-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "A healer can solo it, stay away from his maw and Noxious Breath won't hit you. Then simply keep Remulos up (shouldn't be hard at 80) and let the guards' DPS bring him down.", "creationdate": "2009-01-12T22:21:21-06:00", "id": 72340, "rating": 2, "commentid": 551291, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Arbron", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "soloed him today as a Retribution Paladin, just kept Seal of Wisdom up and only Judged Wisdom to let Remulos keep aggro and healed him anytime he needed while meleeing Eranikus", "creationdate": "2009-02-02T19:21:58-06:00", "id": 77472, "rating": 3, "commentid": 551291, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Lotharemas", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-02-18T15:25:08-06:00", 2, "170332"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 579219, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "BalancedBreakfas", "body": "i druidported to moonglade to turn in some Lunar Festival coins of ancestery and immediately started getting hit by his shades, i somehow was the first one to hit him and wound up tanking the whole fight...\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nin my [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=21538]Festive Pink Dress[/url]", "date": "2009-01-24T22:56:06-06:00", "rating": 62, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I had much the same happen to me, except that I was in full Ulduar gear... and soon after I tagged him I realized that very likely I had messed up someone's extremely difficult and lengthy quest line. So to avoid bad karma, I ran out in the hopes that it would revert the tag to the group that had actually started the event. Worse scenario: he resets and reverts. Worst case: My tag didn't expire, and NOBODY gets credit, since I flew out and didn't have the quest in my log anyway.", "creationdate": "2009-08-23T23:21:08-05:00", "id": 421856, "rating": 0, "commentid": 579219, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Alfador", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
