{"commentv2": 1, "number": 20, "id": 685371, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Ranma11788", "body": "How or why is it that even now, LONG after the AQ gates have been opened, do we see the server wide announcment?\r\n\r\nIs it a glitch, or have people just been holding onto the quest that long or something?", "date": "2009-04-19T22:30:49-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The announcement is made server-wide when Eranikus is defeated for the Emerald part of the Scepter quest line.  The only part of the quest line that is time-dependent on the opening of the gates is the part where bang the gong and get the special mount and title \"Scarab Lord.\"  So it is possible for people to complete the quest and defeat Eranikus indefinitely... or whenever Blizz decides we're having too much fun with it.", "creationdate": "2009-04-21T23:54:27-05:00", "id": 93025, "rating": 4, "commentid": 685371, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "odayaka", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 702008, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Vdemise", "body": "Yes, most healing classes can solo this quest in the Emerald Scepter chain. Although I am not a Resto Shaman, Elemental does the job just fine.\r\n\r\nDied at 30% though because of the acid breath but both the Tyrande and Remulos kept me up along with some of my healing (Healing Wave, Lesser Healing Wave and Chain Heal) but popped up and was free to DPS until the event completed.", "date": "2009-05-02T00:02:33-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
